        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 3:18PM EDT by NWS State College PA</headline>
        <description>At 318 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ligonier, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Westmont around 325 PM EDT.
Davidsville, Dale, and East Conemaugh around 330 PM EDT.
Scalp Level, Windber, and Paint around 335 PM EDT.
Dunlo, Salix-Beauty Line Park, and St. Michael around 340 PM EDT.
Beaverdale-Lloydell around 345 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Benson, Spring Hill,
University Of Pittsburgh - Johnstown, Elim, and Johnstown Flood
National Memorial Historic Site.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
